Cardano is an ambition project, but is still an unproven and has not yet been tested in full unlike competitor  platforms.
Cardano puts forward an impressive plan and long-term vision for its blockchain and cryptocurrency but it is still early days, many of which are yet to be implemented. 
Many of the claims Cardano makes are theoretical as the blockchain is still developing. While its initial use case is as a cryptocurrency, Cardano’s blockchain intends to expand beyond coins into a control layer that will provide services absent in the cryptocurrency ecosystem today. Given that it is still early days, much depends on their execution of the vision.

Over the years, the Cardano team has missed multiple deadlines on its roadmap, taking a deliberately slow route and forgoing the 1st mover advantage Ethereum had. Given Cardano is a 3rd generation blockchain it’s hard to fault and find suggestions for improvement. They had the advantage of seeing issues within the domain and made implementations to meet the arising needs of the User and resolve pervious issues the User encountered to ensure long-lasting future for Cardano. 

Despite the many benefits of Cardano experts state that demand for ADA is low, since the team hasn’t yet implemented a lot of projects due to incomplete smart-contract and token standards, So, it’s still hard to use for people who want to run their Initial Coin Offerings (ICOs) and implement asset tokenization, this is one of Cardano main issues and why Cardano is losing its position among its main competitors Ethereum and Solana 



